Kenny. you shoot it. Doug. you direct.

241
00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:58.337
Huh? Come on. What do you say?

242
00:13:58.421 --> 00:14:00.590
I mean. it's a wonderful idea
in theory. but…

243
00:14:00.673 --> 00:14:04.093
I'm in! I can get time off from work.

244
00:14:04.177 --> 00:14:05.803
Yes. you can. Kenny. Sweet!

245
00:14:05.887 --> 00:14:09.474
Kenny. what are you talking about?
You're in? He's not… No. He's not in.

246
00:14:09.557 --> 00:14:13.186
He says one thing and you're in already.
You're going to the Amazon.

247
00:14:13.269 --> 00:14:15.521
- He's not in.
- What do you say. Claire?

248
00:14:15.605 --> 00:14:17.148
- I… I just…
- Come on.

249
00:14:17.231 --> 00:14:19.025
I don't know
if I'm in the right headspace…

250
00:14:19.108 --> 00:14:20.502
- Of course you are.
- …with the divorce.

251
00:14:20.526 --> 00:14:21.962
Of course you're not
in the right headspace.

252
00:14:21.986 --> 00:14:24.238
That's the best headspace.
Are you kidding me?

253
00:14:24.322 --> 00:14:27.575
Come on. it's like <i>Eat Pray Love</i>
and… shit.

254
00:14:27.658 --> 00:14:28.659
Come on.

255
00:14:29.660 --> 00:14:31.412
You know what? I'm in.

256
00:14:31.496 --> 00:14:32.955
- What? Really?
- Yes

257
00:14:33.039 --> 00:14:33.915
- Sweet.
- Yeah.

258
00:14:33.998 --> 00:14:36.334
I mean. my life is totally shit anyway so…

259
00:14:36.417 --> 00:14:38.294
- God. I'm so happy to hear that.
- Hmm.

260
00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:40.880
I mean. not that your life is shit.
but that you're in.

261
00:14:41.381 --> 00:14:43.007
Besides. as soon as Doug says yes.

262
00:14:43.091 --> 00:14:45.027
we'll probably need you
to finance this whole thing.

263
00:14:45.051 --> 00:14:46.677
- What?
- Thank you.

264
00:14:46.761 --> 00:14:47.761
Doug?

265
00:14:51.849 --> 00:14:53.935
Griff. I'm sorry.

266
00:14:54.519 --> 00:14:58.272
I got responsibilities.
I got Malie. Charlie. my job.

267
00:14:58.356 --> 00:15:00.775
I know. Making. uh. wedding videos.

268
00:15:00.858 --> 00:15:02.276
Films. Right.

269
00:15:03.069 --> 00:15:04.404
It's a good life. you know?

270
00:15:05.113 --> 00:15:06.656
It's a B. B+ life.

271
00:15:08.241 --> 00:15:09.700
B. B+ life?

272
00:15:11.285 --> 00:15:12.495
It's a good life.

273
00:15:14.122 --> 00:15:15.498
Do you remember when we were kids

274
00:15:15.581 --> 00:15:17.226
and we would stay up
till 4:00 in the morning.

275
00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:19.530
hanging out in your mom's basement
watching horror movies?

276
00:15:20.378 --> 00:15:22.130
Scaring the shit out of ourselves.

277
00:15:22.213 --> 00:15:24.465
<i>Texas Chainsaw</i> on. like. repeat.

278
00:15:24.549 --> 00:15:26.884
Now we have the chance
to make one ourselves.

279
00:15:27.885 --> 00:15:30.763
Dude. it's what we dreamed about
ever since we were little kids.

280
00:15:32.515 --> 00:15:33.683
I hear ya.

281
00:15:34.684 --> 00:15:36.936
But we're not kids anymore. Griff.

282
00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:38.855
I'm sorry.

283
00:15:41.149 --> 00:15:42.859
Yeah. I know. All right.

284
00:15:43.860 --> 00:15:44.902
I just…

285
00:15:45.820 --> 00:15:46.988
I get it. I do.

286
00:15:47.905 --> 00:15:49.073
I get it.

287
00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:56.914
Still watching <i>The Quatch</i>.

288
00:16:02.253 --> 00:16:04.755
Charlie. why don't you go
check on those cookies?

289
00:16:04.839 --> 00:16:07.300
Okay. but I'm pausing it. so…

290
00:16:08.342 --> 00:16:09.343
Don't touch it.

291
00:16:10.428 --> 00:16:12.513
Gonna need some ice-cold milch with that.

292
00:16:12.597 --> 00:16:13.848
You got it.

293
00:16:15.057 --> 00:16:16.559
- What are you doing?
- What?

294
00:16:16.642 --> 00:16:17.977
Just go make the movie.

295
00:16:18.060 --> 00:16:19.353
Malie.

296
00:16:19.437 --> 00:16:21.981
Come on. Every time you watch this thing.
you light up.

297
00:16:22.064 --> 00:16:24.775
Like I haven't seen you light up
in a long time.

298
00:16:24.859 --> 00:16:28.654
So what? I'm supposed to chase
some Hollywood fantasy I had as a kid?

299
00:16:28.738 --> 00:16:30.948
Waste a bunch of money and time.
and for what?

300
00:16:31.032 --> 00:16:33.242
In the end. what's it gonna change?

301
00:16:35.828 --> 00:16:36.829
Okay.

302
00:16:38.206 --> 00:16:39.207
Okay.

303
00:16:39.749 --> 00:16:40.750
Okay.

304
00:16:48.382 --> 00:16:50.510
<i>We hope you come to celebrate…</i>

305
00:16:50.593 --> 00:16:51.593
<i>As we become…</i>

306
00:16:51.636 --> 00:16:53.012
<i>The Hansons.</i>

307
00:16:54.597 --> 00:16:56.307
Holy shit.

308
00:17:08.361 --> 00:17:10.530
<i>♪…what will it be? ♪</i>

309
00:17:11.781 --> 00:17:16.869
♪ <i>I don't want to wait</i>
<i>For our lives to be over </i> ♪

310
00:17:16.953 --> 00:17:19.455
What am I singing?

311
00:17:20.957 --> 00:17:21.958
Hey. dude.

312
00:17:24.126 --> 00:17:26.337
I don't want to wait. man.

313
00:17:27.421 --> 00:17:30.675
Our lives could be. like… over.

314
00:17:31.300 --> 00:17:32.593
What are you talking about?

315
00:17:32.677 --> 00:17:36.180
The <i>Anaconda </i>thing.
You were serious. right?

316
00:17:37.181 --> 00:17:38.224
Yes. very.

317
00:17:38.307 --> 00:17:39.517
Then let's do it.

318
00:17:40.726 --> 00:17:42.520
Let's reboot <i>Anaconda.</i>

319
00:17:43.437 --> 00:17:45.481
Yes! Yes.

320
00:18:03.916 --> 00:18:05.876
{\an8}<i>♪ My anaconda don't ♪</i>

321
00:18:06.669 --> 00:18:09.839
All right. budget-wise. soup to nuts.
what does it cost to get this thing made?

322
00:18:09.922 --> 00:18:13.843
I figure we need three weeks of shooting.
Some VFX. some SFX.

323
00:18:13.926 --> 00:18:17.138
a riverboat. a riverboat captain.
travel to and from a jungle.

324
00:18:17.221 --> 00:18:20.891
and a gigantic real snake.
preferably a rental.

325
00:18:20.975 --> 00:18:22.476
- Rental. copy.
- All in.

326
00:18:22.560 --> 00:18:24.520
two. two-and-a-half million dollars.

327
00:18:24.604 --> 00:18:26.188
That sounds right.

328
00:18:26.272 --> 00:18:30.568
We've approved a loan for you for up to…

329
00:18:30.651 --> 00:18:32.320
$9.400.

330
00:18:32.903 --> 00:18:33.779
Yes!

331
00:18:33.863 --> 00:18:36.574
I've revised the budget down to

332
00:18:36.657 --> 00:18:37.992
$43.000 all in.

333
00:18:38.075 --> 00:18:39.243
That sounds more right.

334
00:18:39.327 --> 00:18:41.221
<i>Now. the film does have</i>
<i>to be scary. right?</i>

335
00:18:41.245 --> 00:18:45.249
Terrifying. But it can't just be about
a giant snake killing people.

336
00:18:45.333 --> 00:18:46.584
- Exactly.
- You know?

337
00:18:46.667 --> 00:18:48.711
It has to be about something. right?

338
00:18:48.794 --> 00:18:49.795
Right.

339
00:18:50.671 --> 00:18:52.089
I mean…

340
00:18:52.173 --> 00:18:53.215
- Themes.
- Themes.

341
00:18:54.634 --> 00:18:55.968
- Come on.
- Like grief.

342
00:18:56.052 --> 00:18:56.927
What about revenge?

343
00:18:57.011 --> 00:18:59.680
In terms of themes.
that's like one of the top ones.

344
00:18:59.764 --> 00:19:01.599
- Oh. my God. I got a good one.
- Hit me.

345
00:19:01.682 --> 00:19:03.601
Intergenerational trauma.

346
00:19:03.684 --> 00:19:05.728
I love intergenerational trauma.

347
00:19:05.811 --> 00:19:07.492
Who doesn't love intergenerational trauma?

348
00:19:07.521 --> 00:19:09.732
- It's the best.
- We're onto something here.

349
00:19:17.865 --> 00:19:19.617
This is a masterpiece.

350
00:19:19.700 --> 00:19:21.535
You're a goddamn genius. I love it.

351
00:19:21.619 --> 00:19:23.037
- Don't change a word.
- Not a word.

352
00:19:23.120 --> 00:19:25.474
Dude. you killed it. It's scary.
emotional. it's funny when it needs to be.

353
00:19:25.498 --> 00:19:27.541
- Romantic.
- Dude. thank you.

354
00:19:27.625 --> 00:19:28.751
Hey. Doug…

355
00:19:29.710 --> 00:19:34.215
I know that we had our little dust up. but…

356
00:19:35.424 --> 00:19:37.635
I need to shoot this film. man.

357
00:19:37.718 --> 00:19:38.719
Dustup?

358
00:19:39.470 --> 00:19:42.890
Yeah. He fired me
from the wedding video stuff

359
00:19:42.973 --> 00:19:45.309
'cause I got a little wasted.

360
00:19:45.393 --> 00:19:47.103
He knocked over the wedding cake.

361
00:19:48.104 --> 00:19:50.940
- But I'm dealing with it.
- Like. getting sober?

362
00:19:51.023 --> 00:19:52.024
Yes.

363
00:19:52.108 --> 00:19:54.193
Well. I mean. Buffalo sober.

364
00:19:54.276 --> 00:19:56.570
- Buffalo sober?
- Mm-hmm. Just beer and wine.

365
00:19:58.155 --> 00:20:01.826
And then some of the lighter liquors.
But definitely not all of 'em.

366
00:20:03.244 --> 00:20:04.244
I'm proud of you.

367
00:20:05.705 --> 00:20:06.705
Doug?

368
00:20:08.874 --> 00:20:11.627
If I'm being honest.
I enabled you a little bit.

369
00:20:11.711 --> 00:20:14.171
Of course you get a second chance.
Let's do this.

370
00:20:15.089 --> 00:20:16.132
- Nice!
- Thank you. man.

371
00:20:16.215 --> 00:20:18.759
Car's here.

372
00:20:18.843 --> 00:20:22.555
And you have the Mefloquine. right?
You only take that once a week.

373
00:20:22.638 --> 00:20:25.015
- Hey. Dad. I almost forgot.
- Hmm?

374
00:20:25.099 --> 00:20:29.270
- Talk to me.
- But I got you… this.

375
00:20:29.353 --> 00:20:30.771
What?

376
00:20:30.855 --> 00:20:32.064
I know. Pretty sick.

377
00:20:32.732 --> 00:20:35.401
"World's greatest Doug."

378
00:20:35.484 --> 00:20:38.237
- I thought it should say. "Dad."
- Whatever. man. it's funny.

379
00:20:38.320 --> 00:20:40.531
I love it. It's much better.

380
00:21:17.943 --> 00:21:19.612
- So it begins.
- Yeah!

381
00:21:20.279 --> 00:21:21.197
- Oh. yeah.
- All right

382
00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:22.281
- Whoo!
- Made it.

383
00:21:23.449 --> 00:21:26.009
- Whoa. We're here.
- That's what I'm talkin' about!

384
00:21:26.035 --> 00:21:28.162
- Brasília!
- Oh.

385
00:21:28.245 --> 00:21:30.831
So. hey. I was reading about anacondas
on the plane.

386
00:21:30.915 --> 00:21:33.793
Basically.
they wait in the water for days.

387
00:21:33.876 --> 00:21:36.879
stalking their prey.
never moving. just waiting.

388
00:21:36.962 --> 00:21:38.047
and then when a prey comes…

389
00:21:39.089 --> 00:21:40.007
…snatch and grab.

390
00:21:40.090 --> 00:21:42.811
Thousand pounds of pressure.
Think you're gonna get away? You're not.

391
00:21:42.885 --> 00:21:45.721
Crushing you. Oxygen leaving your lungs.

392
00:21:47.389 --> 00:21:48.933
Oh. God. it's terrible.

393
00:21:49.016 --> 00:21:51.393
- So. like in the movie <i>Anaconda</i>.
- Yeah. exactly.

394
00:21:51.477 --> 00:21:52.561
So it's real?

395
00:21:52.645 --> 00:21:53.938
Yeah. it's all real.

396
00:21:55.856 --> 00:21:59.026
Very real.

397
00:21:59.109 --> 00:22:01.779
There's this story about this woman…

398
00:22:02.321 --> 00:22:03.405
God bless her.

399
00:22:04.073 --> 00:22:06.951
The snake wraps around her so tight…

400
00:22:08.619 --> 00:22:10.079
The eyeballs just…

401
00:22:11.831 --> 00:22:13.749
- No.
- No way.

402
00:22:13.833 --> 00:22:16.877
- Yeah. it was my grandmother. Sylvana.
- Shit.

403
00:22:17.419 --> 00:22:20.089
Horrible grandmother. But still sad.

404
00:22:20.589 --> 00:22:21.589
Huh.

405
00:22:21.632 --> 00:22:22.800
I'm sorry. who are you?

406
00:22:23.467 --> 00:22:26.220
Oh. I'm sorry. Carlos Santiago.
Yeah. you can call me Santiago.

407
00:22:26.303 --> 00:22:28.556
- Hey! It's Kenny.
- Yeah. hey.

408
00:22:28.639 --> 00:22:31.183
- Kenny from the phone. Hey.
- Kenny. Kenny. hey.

409
00:22:31.267 --> 00:22:33.394
- Hi.
- Yeah. this is our snake handler.

410
00:22:33.477 --> 00:22:34.353
Oh!

411
00:22:34.436 --> 00:22:36.248
- Thank God.
- He's supposed to be the best.

412
00:22:36.272 --> 00:22:38.357
No. "Supposed to be"?
We have a joker here.

413
00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:40.859
No. I am the best. Yes.

414
00:22:40.943 --> 00:22:42.170
- Oh. That's good.
- Yeah.

415
00:22:42.194 --> 00:22:44.280
So. welcome to Brazil.

416
00:22:45.406 --> 00:22:46.782
Let's meet the snake.

417
00:22:59.211 --> 00:23:01.672
Go around. we'll find her.

418
00:23:20.316 --> 00:23:23.193
When I found him.
he was dying of starvation.

419
00:23:23.986 --> 00:23:28.282
His food supply destroyed by gold miners
who put mercury in the river.

420
00:23:28.365 --> 00:23:31.201
- Gold miners?
- Gold mining poisons our land.

421
00:23:31.994 --> 00:23:34.330
Their greed almost killed my snake.

422
00:23:34.872 --> 00:23:39.168
- Oh.
- But I fed him. I nursed him back to life.

423
00:23:39.251 --> 00:23:42.796
and in many ways. he did the same for me.

424
00:23:42.880 --> 00:23:45.507
Ah. yes. A tale as old as time.

425
00:23:45.591 --> 00:23:46.842
Saved by a snake.

426
00:23:49.762 --> 00:23:51.180
What's your name?

427
00:23:51.263 --> 00:23:52.264
What's… Uh. Griff.

428
00:23:52.348 --> 00:23:54.516
Okay. Griff. He's not only a snake.

429
00:23:55.225 --> 00:23:57.394
He's my tiny giant. my friend.

430
00:23:58.312 --> 00:24:02.107
One of the most important creatures
of the herpetological world.

431
00:24:02.691 --> 00:24:04.276
No. of course… I… Sure.

432
00:24:04.360 --> 00:24:07.112
I didn't… I wasn't trying to… I… Yes.

433
00:24:07.196 --> 00:24:10.282
Okay. Let me introduce you.

434
00:24:13.744 --> 00:24:15.037
Heitor.

435
00:24:15.120 --> 00:24:17.915
- Heitor?
- Oh. my goodness.

436
00:24:17.998 --> 00:24:19.583
Hey. cutie.

437
00:24:19.667 --> 00:24:21.669
- Oh. no. Not cutie.
- Oh. my…

438
00:24:21.752 --> 00:24:23.587
Oh…

439
00:24:23.671 --> 00:24:26.382
Oh. hell. yes! This thing is nuts!

440
00:24:26.465 --> 00:24:29.802
There are rumors of 'condas even bigger.

441
00:24:29.885 --> 00:24:32.554
Maybe four or five times this size.

442
00:24:33.972 --> 00:24:35.158
Go ahead. Kenny from the phone.

443
00:24:35.182 --> 00:24:38.435
Um. is it true that they
regurgitate their prey?

444
00:24:38.519 --> 00:24:40.396
Um. sometimes.

445
00:24:40.479 --> 00:24:42.356
I mean. if you're lucky.

446
00:24:42.439 --> 00:24:44.066
you die right away because of

447
00:24:44.149 --> 00:24:45.442
suffocation.

448
00:24:46.068 --> 00:24:50.072
But only the unlucky ones survive.

449
00:24:50.155 --> 00:24:51.365
Unlucky?

450
00:24:53.033 --> 00:24:57.413
Yeah. because then
you might actually be conscious

451
00:24:57.496 --> 00:25:01.291
when the snake comes back
to finish you off.

452
00:25:01.917 --> 00:25:03.669
- Gotcha.
- Ooh.

453
00:25:03.752 --> 00:25:04.795
Better to die.

454
00:25:14.054 --> 00:25:16.765
- Look at that boat!
- This is money in the bank. baby.

455
00:25:42.499 --> 00:25:44.334
Hey. Let me ask you a question.

456
00:25:44.418 --> 00:25:46.670
- Um. our snake guy…
- Mmm?

457
00:25:47.296 --> 00:25:50.132
…does he seem kind of bat shit crazy?

458
00:25:50.215 --> 00:25:52.509
I mean. he's best friends with a snake.

459
00:25:52.593 --> 00:25:54.028
- Of course he's a little quirky.
- Yeah.

460
00:25:54.052 --> 00:25:55.053
But I like him.

461
00:25:55.137 --> 00:25:55.971
- Really?
- Yeah.

462
00:25:56.054 --> 00:25:57.055
But then again.

463
00:25:57.139 --> 00:25:59.183
I used up all my vacation days

464
00:25:59.266 --> 00:26:02.478
to come make a self-financed snake movie
with you three. so…

465
00:26:02.561 --> 00:26:04.748
- Yeah. your judgment is really off.
- My judgment is off.

466
00:26:04.772 --> 00:26:05.874
- It always has been.
- Exactly.

467
00:26:05.898 --> 00:26:07.917
Anybody talk to the captain?
It's time to shoot.

468
00:26:07.941 --> 00:26:09.693
I'll reach out again. boss.

469
00:26:11.445 --> 00:26:13.113
Hi. guys. My name is Ana.

470
00:26:13.197 --> 00:26:15.032
I believe you spoke
to my father on the phone?

471
00:26:15.616 --> 00:26:17.201
Bruno? That's your dad?

472
00:26:17.910 --> 00:26:19.012
Yeah. he sends his apologies.

473
00:26:19.036 --> 00:26:20.954
- but he's at the hospital.
- Oh.

474
00:26:21.038 --> 00:26:22.956
- Oh. I'm sorry.
- Unfortunately.

475
00:26:23.040 --> 00:26:24.680
you'll have to make other accommodations.

476
00:26:24.750 --> 00:26:27.878
'cause I need to take this boat upriver
for a routine service.

477
00:26:27.961 --> 00:26:29.421
But I can assure you a full refund.

478
00:26:29.505 --> 00:26:30.339
No. wait. Wait.

479
00:26:30.422 --> 00:26:32.466
- Everything else is booked.
- Yeah.

480
00:26:32.549 --> 00:26:34.343
And… and we're gonna shoot a movie.

481
00:26:34.426 --> 00:26:36.303
It's a… it's a reboot of <i>Anaconda</i>.

482
00:26:36.386 --> 00:26:38.114
Technically.
it's more of a reimagining. but...

483
00:26:38.138 --> 00:26:40.015
It's actually more of a spiritual sequel.

484
00:26:40.098 --> 00:26:41.183
Good for you.

485
00:26:41.266 --> 00:26:43.119
- There's gotta be a way. right?
- We can crew the boat.

486
00:26:43.143 --> 00:26:44.019
There's nothing I can do…

487
00:26:44.102 --> 00:26:47.773
We have dreamed of making
this film together our entire lives.

488
00:26:47.856 --> 00:26:50.234
Please. I am begging you.

489
00:26:50.317 --> 00:26:52.277
- Please.
- Help us find another way.

490
00:26:52.361 --> 00:26:54.071
- Let's do this. but fast.
